setup_twitter_oauth(consumer_key, consumer_secret, access_token, access_secret)
## [1] "Using direct authentication"
user_name <- "REI"

# Download tweets from user profile
tweets <- userTimeline(user_name, n = 500)

# Convert tweets to a data frame
tweets.df <- twListToDF(tweets)

dim(tweets.df)
## [1] 450  16
tweets_txt <- tweets.df$text
# chartr | tolower | toupper | casefold | gsub
# remove retweet entities
tweets_clean = gsub("(RT|via)((?:\\b\\W*@\\w+)+)", "", tweets_txt)
# remove Atpeople
tweeets_clean = gsub("@\\w+", "", tweets_clean)
# remove punctuation symbols
tweets_clean = gsub("[[:punct:]]", "", tweets_clean)
# remove numbers
tweets_clean = gsub("[[:digit:]]", "", tweets_clean)
# remove links
tweets_clean = gsub("http\\w+", "", tweets_clean)
# corpus
tweets_corpus = Corpus(VectorSource(tweets_clean))

# convert to lower case
tweets_corpus = tm_map(tweets_corpus, tolower)
# remove stoprwords
tweeets_corpus = tm_map(tweets_corpus, removeWords, c(stopwords("english"), "rei"))
# remove extra white-spaces
tweets_corpus = tm_map(tweets_corpus, stripWhitespace)

tweets_corpus = tm_map(tweets_corpus, PlainTextDocument)
# term-document matrix
tdm = TermDocumentMatrix(tweets_corpus)

# convert as matrix
m = as.matrix(tdm)
# remove sparse terms (word frequency > 90% percentile)
wf = rowSums(m)
m1 = m[wf>quantile(wf,probs=0.9), ]

# remove columns with all zeros
m1 = m1[,colSums(m1)!=0]

# for convenience, every matrix entry must be binary (0 or 1)
m1[m1 > 1] = 1
# distance matrix with binary distance
m1dist = dist(m1, method="binary")

# cluster with ward method
clus1 = hclust(m1dist, method="ward")
## The "ward" method has been renamed to "ward.D"; note new "ward.D2"
# plot dendrogram
plot(clus1, cex=0.7)

# correspondance analysis
rei_ca = CA(m1, graph=FALSE)

# default plot of words
plot(rei_ca$row$coord, type="n", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", xlab="", ylab="")
text(rei_ca$row$coord[,1], rei_ca$row$coord[,2], labels=rownames(m1),
   col=hsv(0,0,0.6,0.5))
title(main="@user_name Correspondence Analysis of tweet words", cex.main=1)

# partitioning around medoids iwth 6 clusters
k = 6

# pam clustering
rei_pam = pam(rei_ca$row$coord[,1:2], k)

# get clusters
clusters = rei_pam$clustering
## first we need to define a color palette
#gbrew = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")

## I like to use hsv encoding

# create data frame
rei_words_df = data.frame(
words = rownames(m1),
dim1 = rei_ca$row$coord[,1],
dim2 = rei_ca$row$coord[,2],
freq = rowSums(m1),
cluster = as.factor(clusters))

# plot
ggplot(rei_words_df, aes(x=dim1, y=dim2, label=words)) +
geom_text(aes(size=freq, colour=cluster), alpha=0.7) +
scale_size_continuous(breaks=seq(20,80,by=10), range=c(3,8)) +
scale_colour_manual(values=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")) +
labs(x="", y="")
